            I’m a Ph.D. candidate in the Department of Government at
            Harvard University. I do research on lobbying and campaign
            contributions, both empirical and theoretical. I am
            interested in political economic theory more broadly.
            See my research, my CV, my teaching slides, and my old blog.
            
            
